<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-084-309 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 097 401</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  August 6 1991 v5 n27 p8(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New developments from APDA: annual subscription fees dropped.andO;(Apple Programmers and Developers Association)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Williams, Wade.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (Services).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Topic:     Apple Programmers and Developers AssociationUser GroupsApplications Programming.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Wade WilliamsandM;Cupertino, Calif.andP;  -- Apple this week will announce that it has dropped theannual subscription fees for its developer group, APDA.andM;APDA is notifying current customers of the change and will consider refundingsubscription fees on a case-by-case basis, depending on the date the customerjoined, according to Apple.andP;  Subscription fees had ranged from $20 to $35.andM;&quot;We're eliminating the annual subscription charge so we can provide eveneasier access to our development tools,&quot; said Kirk Loevner, director ofApple's Developer Services.andP;  Loevner said APDA also will offer specialbundles in the future to help new developers get started.andM;In addition, a new catalog has been introduced that replaces APDAlog.andP;  Thenew 144-page APDA Tools Catalog contains color photographs, screen shots anddetailed descriptions of more than 300 Apple and third-party products.andP;  APDAwill publish the catalog semiannually, along with quarterly updates.andM;Apple also has dissolved Developer Tools Express, a separate developmentgroup that did not offer prerelease or beta products.andP;  Its customers will begiven membership in APDA.andP;  All customers will be required to sign APDA'sterms and conditions form to purchase prerelease products.andM;APDA is at 20525 Mariani Ave., M/S 33-G, Cupertino, Calif.andP;  95014.andP;  Phone(408) 562-3910 or (800) 282-2732; fax (408) 562-3971.andO;</TEXT></DOC>